##gff-version 2
##description: Gold standard test cases for base splicing events (GTF format)
##date: 2026-02-09
# TEST CASE 1: Simple Exon Skipping (SE)
# T1 has 3 exons, T2 skips the middle exon
# TEST CASE 2: Alternative 5' Splice Site (A5SS)
# Two exons share 3' end (1700) but have different 5' starts
# TEST CASE 3: Alternative 3' Splice Site (A3SS)
# Two exons share 5' start (5000) but have different 3' ends
# TEST CASE 4: Intron Retention (IR)
# T2 has large exon that spans T1's two exons
# TEST CASE 5: Alternative TSS (Alt_TSS)
# First exons start at different positions (>20bp apart)
# TEST CASE 6: Alternative TES (Alt_TES)
# Last exons end at different positions (>20bp apart)
# TEST CASE 7: Monoexonic IR (IR_monoexonic)
# T1 is monoexonic and spans T2's three exons
# TEST CASE 8: Monoexonic + First-only sharing start boundary
# Edge case: monoexonic shares start with multi-exonic first exon
# TEST CASE 9: TSS within tolerance
# First exons with starts within 20bp (should be grouped for TSS detection)
# TEST CASE 10: Multiple events in one transition
# T1 vs T2 has both SE and A3SS
# TEST CASE 11: IR spanning 3 contiguous exons (exact boundaries)
# T1 has 3 exons, T2 has one spanning exon matching first start and third end
# TEST CASE 12: IR spanning 2 contiguous exons (partial overlap, no exact boundaries)
# T1 has 2 exons, T2 has spanning exon that overlaps but doesn't match boundaries
# TEST CASE 13: Partial_IR (A5SS pattern with ≥100bp difference, multi-exon)
# T1 has exon 25000-25100, then 25300-25500 (total 300bp)
# T2 has exon 25000-25220, then 25300-25500 (adds 120bp in first exon)
# Shared START, different END at internal exon → Partial_IR
# TEST CASE 14: Partial_IR (A3SS pattern with ≥100bp difference, multi-exon)
# T1 has exon 26000-26200, then 26400-26600
# T2 has exon 26000-26200, then 26280-26600 (adds 120bp in second exon)
# Different START, shared END at internal exon → Partial_IR
# TEST CASE 15: Deduplication test (3 isoforms with same Alt_TSS pattern)
# T1 has first exon 27000-27500, T2 and T3 both have 27100-27500
# Should detect one Alt_TSS event with comparison_isoforms=[T2, T3]
chr_test	test	exon	1000	1200	.	+	.	gene_id "TEST_SE_Basic"; transcript_id "TEST_SE_Basic_T1"; exon_number "1";
chr_test	test	exon	1500	1700	.	+	.	gene_id "TEST_SE_Basic"; transcript_id "TEST_SE_Basic_T1"; exon_number "2";
chr_test	test	exon	2000	2200	.	+	.	gene_id "TEST_SE_Basic"; transcript_id "TEST_SE_Basic_T1"; exon_number "3";
chr_test	test	exon	1000	1200	.	+	.	gene_id "TEST_SE_Basic"; transcript_id "TEST_SE_Basic_T2"; exon_number "1";
